Edited January 9, 2023 by Skywavestar

well , after so long, a new work is finally good enough to show to everyone here, for me. This is a SSTO with a simple design that I could make it into a paper model within my summer holiday.(I don't have a color printer so I have to print it in black and white)

After so long (again), the papers' original download site has lost its efficacy. Thank to the unknown bro and https://archive.org/, I managed to download the papers from their snapshot.

In fact, since this topic was created, it has been almost ten years, even longer than half of my life. It is really lucky for me to discover this valuable project and turn it into reality again. Great appreciation to the riser of this topic @arc5555

Found the topic in 2017 while I was looking for something to kill time outside computer.
First I made small, basic rocket, then bigger tin can with boosters and satellite. A few parts were incomplete and needed reconstruction. It was printed on old inkjet printer, only black. In grays, with paper edges painted with pencil to hide them, and a bit of wobbliness, it looked quite nice, like 3d pencil drawing. I only have two takes on engine and the satellite left.
